OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777420987
OL,3,CKing hails 'truly unique' alliance in
OL,4,Cspeech to US Congress
OL,6,F"Whatever our differences, whatever
OL,7,Fdisagreements we may have, we stand
OL,8,Funited in our commitment to uphold
OL,9,Fdemocracy, to protect all our people
OL,10,Ffrom harm, and to salute the courage
OL,11,Fof those who daily risk their lives in
OL,12,Fthe service of our countries."
OL,14,FThere were murmurs of approval from a
OL,15,Fnumber of Democrats when the King told
OL,16,Fthe chamber: "America's words carry
OL,17,Fweight and meaning, as they have since
OL,18,FIndependence.
OL,20,F"The actions of this great nation
OL,21,Fmatter even more."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@^O]xD@NOU|D@AOU}D@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
