OL,3,CKing hails 'truly unique' alliance in
OL,4,Cspeech to US Congress
OL,6,FCharles received applause and cheers
OL,7,Fwhen he described America's Founding
OL,8,FFathers as "bold and imaginative
OL,9,Frebels with a cause" and made the
OL,10,FSenators and Members of the House of
OL,11,FRepresentatives laugh when he added:
OL,12,F"Two hundred and fifty years ago ` or,
OL,13,Fas we say in the United Kingdom, just
OL,14,Fthe other day ` they declared
OL,15,FIndependence."
OL,17,FThe chamber gave 12 brief standing
OL,18,Fovations during the King's speech and
OL,19,Falso stood up and applauded for a few
OL,20,Fminutes when he first arrived and made
OL,21,Fhis way to the lectern with the Queen.
OL,26,@pD@LOUqD@TO]tD@AOUwD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
